my fear of talking to women… But sometimes I perservere…

So fun! What a great way to meet new people. I used to like going to the tourist taco/coffee shop in Seattle.

This post was great! loved the ideas. ALso laughing with joy at your tone! you have a winning personality Laura!

Fun! I love that. Popular amenities include public laundries. 95% of people here seem to make washing, drying and folding their childrens clothes very social. Its the place to catch up on all the latest gossip and lifelong friendships are formed every day.

Oh i love meeting Icelandic men in bars especially; they are darling, hardly drunk, often shy, speak english. Check.

Oh well. I have easily emmigrated 3 times and went back all 3 times.

I want to emigrate next time for the long haul…I want out.

cherries berries fell! and they go la la la to the jingle bell band

Just wanted to thank Lisa Jacobs for all her great writing and creative info.

These ideas are awesome! I did move overseas almost ten and a half years ago and miss some of that interaction with new people, but it is hard to build friendships when you rarely see the people you meet outside work in a social setting.

Your comment about dryers and sinks reminded me of a weekend retreat in France I went on in college with my Expi Entrada group (Which is as weird as it sounds, thanks college!)
